Description:
The incumbent is responsible for ensuring that project objectives/ implementation are on track/, ensure implementation and documentation according to donor requirements.Core Responsibilities: Coordinates and follows up on project implementation with concerned support departments; reports any delays or problems hindering the implementation of the project to facilitate daily operations.
 Conducts regular field visits to the targeted areas to monitor and ensure the implementation of project activities.
Monitors and controls financial expenditure of projects, assists in developing alternative plans to utilize balance of funds remaining after the completion of projects;
Collects data and information on the progress of project implementation for use in the monthly monitoring report; to ensure working within the action plan.
Creates and maintains projects database and project master plan, follows up and updates relevant data to produce accurate information and maintains and reports up-to-date information on projects as required;
 Maintains close communication and proactive coordination with donors to follow up on the establishment of project schedule, ensuring conformity with the Programâ€™s plans and priorities;
 Monitors tracks closely the project plan implementation according to time and achieves objectives; and ensures that all project activities and relevant documents are documented/archived according to donor requirements;
 Supports the field team with all documents and information needed; for proper project implantation to ensure that, the project remains on track and production of reports in a timely manner.
Follows up with project clients and mentors periodically ensuring the success of the outcomes that are desired by the project, and the correct implementation of project activities.
Communicates with project partners in the targeted areas, facilitating collaboration and communicating changes and developments on day-to-day activities.
Represents the foundation in an adequate manner in the targeted areas, and with the targeted population, as well as, with different partners and stakeholders.Skills
